pull.title: Move cs_main locking annotations from .cpp to .h

events.message: Move cs_main locking annotations from .cpp to .h

events.body: does this make any difference to the functionality? or is this just better from a documentation point of view?
The locking annotations are only evaluated at compile time, so when they are not in the header file, they are ignored outside of that translation unit.

comments.body: Could move this all the way up (right after the includes?)
